This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with image classification and localization tasks. The use of deep learning models also suggests that it could belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the mention of the ChestX-ray14 dataset suggests that it could belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the potential clinical applications of the proposed method suggest that it could also belong to the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
